# Deep Implementation Plan — Backend + Frontend Integration

## Current State Summary

| Layer | Status |
|---|---|
| **Frontend** | 9 HTML templates with Tailwind CSS, hardcoded data, `window.location.href` navigation |
| **Backend** | [backend/main.py](backend/main.py) — FastAPI serving static HTML pages (GET routes only, no processing) |
| **Logic** | [Final.py](Final.py) — CLI prototype with routing, costing, confidence, DFM logic (not connected) |
| **ML Model** | Not yet trained — **leave placeholder** for future `joblib` model loading |

Design contract: follow [ui.md](ui.md) when wiring frontend behavior. It maps Stitch design folders → `frontend/templates/*` and lists the intended interactions with line numbers.

---

## Architecture Overview

```
Frontend (Jinja2 Templates)
    │  ← HTML forms POST / JS fetch() calls
    ▼
FastAPI Backend (backend/main.py)
    │
    ├── /api/quote           ← POST: receives inputs, returns full quote JSON
    ├── /api/routing         ← POST: receives geometry+inputs, returns routing decision + machine selection + override metadata
    ├── /api/stock           ← POST: receives geometry (incl. bbox)+routing_flags+material, returns stock estimate
    ├── /api/dfm             ← POST: returns ranked DFM suggestions (advisory)
    ├── /api/dfm/simulate    ← POST: simulates an applied suggestion (quote variant) + compare
    │
    ├── Page Routes (GET)    ← Serve templates with Jinja2 context data
    │
    └── Backend Modules (backend/)
         ├── models.py       ← Pydantic schemas (request/response)
         ├── routing.py      ← Process routing rules
         ├── stock.py        ← Stock estimation logic
         ├── cost.py         ← Cost calculation engine
         ├── confidence.py   ← Prediction interval / risk estimation
         ├── explainability.py ← Cost drivers & SHAP placeholder
         ├── dfm.py          ← DFM suggestion engine
         ├── ml_placeholder.py ← ML model stub (returns formula-based time)
         └── sample_parts.py ← 3 sample part definitions
```

---

## Phase 1: Backend Modules

### 1.1 [NEW] `backend/models.py` — Pydantic Schemas

Data contracts between frontend and backend.

```python
# Key models:
class GeometryData        # volume, surface_area, bbox_x/y/z, aspect_ratio, num_faces, num_edges
class UserInputs          # num_holes, num_pockets, max_depth_mm, material, quantity, tolerance_class
class RoutingFlags        # is_turning, is_milling, is_drilling, is_grinding
class MachineSelection    # per-process machine choice (e.g., milling/drilling/...)
class OverrideInfo        # engineer_override, override_note, contradictions_acknowledged
class RoutingDecision     # aligns with Steps/4.md: { routing_decision, machine_assignment, overrides }
class StockEstimate       # stock_shape, stock_volume_cm3, stock_weight_kg, material
class CostBreakdown       # material_cost, machining_cost, setup_cost, overhead_cost, total_cost
class ProcessDetail       # process, machine, time_min, rate_per_hr, cost
class MachiningBreakdown  # process-wise machining minutes + ₹ (canonical: machining_breakdown)
class ConfidenceRange     # low, nominal, high, risk_level, margin_pct
class CostDriver          # feature, impact_value, reason
class DFMSuggestion       # change, savings_inr, reason, icon
class DFMComparison       # quote_original vs quote_modified + assumption deltas (for side-by-side + export)
class FullQuoteResponse   # all above combined
```

---

### 1.2 [NEW] `backend/sample_parts.py` — Sample Part Definitions

Move the 3 sample parts from [Final.py](Final.py) into a reusable module. Each sample provides pre-filled `GeometryData` + `UserInputs` so clicking a sample card on the landing page loads real data.

```python
SAMPLE_PARTS = {
    "steel_bracket":    { geometry: {...}, inputs: {...} },
    "aluminum_housing": { geometry: {...}, inputs: {...} },
    "titanium_shaft":   { geometry: {...}, inputs: {...} },
}
```

---

### 1.3 [NEW] `backend/routing.py` — Process Routing Engine

Port the routing rules from [Final.py](Final.py) and align with [Steps/4.md](Steps/4.md):

| Process | Condition |
|---|---|
| Turning | `aspect_ratio > 2.0` |
| Milling | `num_pockets > 0` OR `surface_area_cm2 > 200` |
| Drilling | `num_holes > 0` |
| Grinding | `tolerance_class ∈ {Fine, Ultra-Fine}` |

**Functions:** `route_processes(geometry, user_inputs) → RoutingDecision`

---

