### 1.6 [NEW] `backend/cost.py` — Cost Calculation Engine

Port from [Steps/10.md](Steps/10.md) and [Final.py](Final.py):

| Component | Formula |
|---|---|
| Material | `stock_weight_kg × price_per_kg × batch_discount` |
| Machining | `machining_time × machine_rate` (allocated across active processes) |
| Setup | `max(2000 / √quantity, 200)` |
| Overhead | (material + machining + setup) × overhead_rate[material] |

**Functions:**
- `material_cost(weight, material, qty) → float`
- `machining_cost(time, routing, machines) → float`
- `setup_cost(qty) → float`
- `overhead_cost(mat, mach, setup, material) → float`
- `calculate_full_quote(...) → CostBreakdown`

---

### 1.7 [NEW] `backend/confidence.py` — Prediction Interval

Port from [Final.py](Final.py) `estimate_confidence()`:

- Base uncertainty 8%, additive factors for Titanium, Ultra-Fine, low qty, high hole count
- Returns `{ low, nominal, high, risk_level, margin_pct }`

> [!NOTE]
> When ML model is ready, replace with tree-based percentile intervals ([Steps/9.md](Steps/9.md)).

